400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/you_me_at_six_end_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/you_me_at_six_end_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/you_me_at_six_end_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/you_me_at_six_end_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/YOU-ME-AT-SIX">您在昨晚（4月4日）的20年职业生涯的六个</a>召唤时间，在伦敦的OVO竞技场温布利（Ovo Arena Wembley）播放了他们的最后一场演出，这是我的六年级职业生涯。从下面的内容中查看setlist，录像等。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/you-me-at-six-tell-josh-franceschi-interview-split-catfish-bottlemen-final-tour-3580717">您六点钟告诉我们他们的分裂：“这是一个严肃的弱者故事”</a></strong></li></ul><p>自2024年1月<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/you-me-at-six-announce-split-and-2025-farewell-tour-now-is-a-good-time-to-call-time-3580114">正式宣布分裂</a>以来，萨里岩五重奏一直在欧洲，澳大利亚，北美和日本的告别秀上。今年2月，他们回到家开始了一场猛mm象37岁的英国巡回赛，在温布利竞技场（Wembley Arena）两晚，结束了。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/you-me-at-six-tell-josh-franceschi-interview-split-catfish-bottlemen-final-tour-3580717">主唱乔什·弗朗切斯（Josh Franceschi）在发行了八张专辑，获得了两张数字，并在三场比赛中获得了三次扣篮，并在Slam Dunk节上发行了标志性的伦敦伦敦和布里克斯顿学院（Brixton Academy）等标志性的伦敦场地，他于去年2月对<em>NME</em>表示</a>，“达到20年的Mark”是您在六个难题中的最后一部分。</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> 15岁那年六点钟就会进来。今天，我今年29岁，我刚刚参加了他们的最后一场演出，就像我在温布利竞技场留下了一部分。<br />这些年来，他们的音乐一直是我所有高潮和（非常）低点的配乐。<br />谢谢您提供的一切<a href="https://twitter.com/youmeatsix?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@youmeatsix</a> <a href="https://t.co/XRsKAQFL2M">pic.twitter.com/xrskaqfl2m</a></p><p> -  Indigo（@Mariia1996） <a href="https://twitter.com/mariia1996/status/1908311689512046762?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2025年4月5日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>对2012年的“罪恶的最后一夜”节目点头 - 乐队在本周之前将标志性的12,500个能力的场地引起了标志性的12,500个能力场地的标题 - “六个六个六个夜晚”也在世界各地直播，并伴随着整个巡回演出的幕后纪录片。两者都<a href="https://driift.live/shows/you-me-at-six" target="_blank" rel="noopener">可以按需观看，</a>直到星期二（4月8日）BST凌晨2点。</p><p>在他们的长期朋友的支持插槽之后<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-xcerts">，Xcerts</a>和Brit-Punk颠覆者<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/KID-KAPICHI">Kid Kapichi</a> ，您在六个踢出诉讼中以其三个最大的热门歌曲开始了，这使忠实的忠实狂奔，带有“呼吸空间”，“ loverboy”，“ Loverboy”和“与我同在”。</p><p> “Have we got any old school You Me At Six fans here tonight?” teased an ever-buoyant Franceschi, toying with the crowd before unleashing breakout hit &#39;Save It For The Bedroom&#39; and the title track of their 2008 debut LP &#39;Take Off Your Colours&#39;.</p><p> “I&#39;m not usually one to get the violins out, but I&#39;ve had some sort of norovirus for the past 10 days,” he later admitted. “I&#39;ve either been throwing up or shitting. Trust me, this is far from perfect, but I will die on this stage before I cancel a show. I was watching you all queue up from my hotel room earlier going, &#39;Wow.&#39;”</p><p> Wembley answered Franceshi&#39;s call for crowd surfers during &#39;Lived A Lie&#39; – taken from their Number One album &#39;Cavalier Youth&#39; (2014) – before &#39;Suckapunch&#39; turned the arena momentarily into a rave. Featuring songs from all eight albums, the setlist exemplified how far You Me At Six&#39;s sound has evolved from its emo and pop-punk roots over the past two decades. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="You Me At Six - Jealous Minds Think Alike (Live, OVO Arena Wembley Night 1, London 2025)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/w3OLZ1FIoQo?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “I&#39;d like to welcome you all to our favourite part of the show,” he continued, teeing up &#39;Jealous Minds Think Alike&#39; and &#39;No Future? Yeah Right&#39; – their 2022 collaboration with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/enter-shikari">Enter Shikari&#39;</a> s Rou Reynolds. “It&#39;s called the mosh pit. Ladies and gentlemen, I need absolute commitment to the cause. I don&#39;t want to see a single phone in the air.”</p><p> Reynolds was not present, as he is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/enter-shikari-rou-reynolds-jeff-waynes-the-war-of-the-worlds-grassroots-venues-3798711">currently on tour with Jeff Wayne&#39;s musical adaptation of <em>The War Of The Worlds</em> .</a> There were no surprise guests over the course of the night, although <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-bring-me-the-horizons-oli-sykes-perform-bite-my-tongue-with-you-me-at-six-in-sheffield-3843487">Bring Me The Horizon&#39;s Oli Sykes joined You Me At Six for their 2011 collaboration &#39;Bite My Tongue</a> &#39; last month (March 3) in Sheffield. <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-biffy-clyro-simon-neil-join-you-me-at-six-on-stage-london-farewell-tour-3851575">Biffy Clyro&#39;s Simon Neil also surprised fans on Wednesday (April 2)</a> , when he joined You Me At Six to perform &#39;No One Does It Better&#39; with the band at O2 Academy Brixton.</p><p> Towards the latter stages of the show, Franceschi opened up about the gravity of the occasion, dedicating &#39;Mixed Emotions (I Didn&#39;t Know How To Tell You What I Was Going Through)&#39; to his bandmates: “Five boys from down the road who spent the last 20 years travelling the globe, playing their songs. Often in pursuit of validation, acceptance and sometimes – on special nights – love.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="You Me At Six - I Miss You [Blink 182 Cover] (Acoustic, Live, OVO Arena Wembley Show 2, London 2025)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OEH8MmbSYgk?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Visibly emotional after performing &#39;Fireworks&#39;, a tearful Franceschi gave guitarist Max Helyer a warm, lengthy embrace, before he recounted the tale of how the band formed 20 years ago, which was interrupted by a brief acoustic rendition of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/blink-182">Blink-182</a> &#39;s &#39;I Miss You&#39;, courtesy of some crowd karaoke. “You know we&#39;ve now got to pay Blink [royalties] for that?!”他开玩笑。 “We&#39;re giving money away and we&#39;re retiring!</p><p> “The year is 2005,” he began. “MSN Messenger and MySpace were the shit. [I went to] a local show in Weybridge Town Hall, there was one man in particular I saw in the crowd – wearing skinny jeans and a Drive-Thru Records t-shirt. Drive Thru Records was home to New Found Glory, Finch, The Starting Line… basically, all the bands we ripped off for &#39;Take Off Your Colours&#39;.”</p><p> He added: “I went and asked him, &#39;Do you play an instrument?… will you be in a band with me?&#39; We couldn&#39;t just be a two-piece, because it only really works if you&#39;re Royal Blood. We saw a man [Matt Barnes, bassist] with long luscious hair and baggy trousers wearing an Incubus t-shirt. Matt, do you know anybody else that plays an instrument?</p><p> “He says, &#39;My next door neighbour [Chris Miller, guitarist] loves &#39;Dirty Sanchez&#39; and &#39;Jackass&#39;, and his favourite bands are Linkin Park and Rage Against The Machine.&#39; Now, we needed a drummer. We said to ourselves, &#39;Don&#39;t look for a drummer, find sex appeal.&#39; I&#39;m talking jawlines, abs, push-ups for breakfast. Turns out the best looking guy we could find was Ryan Gosling… no, it&#39;s Dan Flint, and it turns out he could play the drums.”</p><p> With the 11pm curfew in sight, the time for stories was over, as the band whittled through their signature ballad &#39;Take On The World&#39;, the celebratory grit of &#39;Beautiful Way&#39;, and a three-song encore that began with &#39;Bite My Tongue&#39; and &#39;Reckless&#39; – which received its customary mashup with The Killers&#39; &#39;When You Were Young&#39; – before Franceschi&#39;s final remarks. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="You Me At Six: Bite My Tongue * FINAL SHOW LIVE 4K* [Wembley Arena 04.04.2025]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/G1fRn1M3cFw?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “What do you even say?”他笑了。 “This is a true fucking story about five useless c**ts doing something good with their lives… thank you so much for letting us be your band. For taking us in your headphones, your homes, your hearts. There is only one thing left to say – please stand for your national anthem, &#39;Underdog&#39;.”</p><p> “I think our fans have picked up on the fact that this is a serious underdog story,” Franceschi told <em>NME</em> last year. &#39;Underdog&#39;, therefore, served as a fitting farewell for the band who have called time at the peak of their powers, perhaps unexpectedly completing their biggest UK tour to date. Raising a glass to the crowd as he exited the stage, Franceschi&#39;s final words as You Me At Six frontman were short and sweet. “Just like that, we are dead. See you later.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="You Me At Six: Underdog *LAST EVER SONG, FINAL SHOW 4K* [Wembley Arena 04.04.2025]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HmLubmAPQlk?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><h2> <strong>You Me At Six&#39;s setlist was:</strong></h2><p> &#39;Room To Breathe&#39;<br /> &#